SIMPLE: onchocerciasis
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: onchocerciasis
<hw>onchocerciasis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
infection with nematodes of the genus <gen>Onchocerca</gen>, especially
<causedby><spn>Onchocerca volvulus</spn></causedby>. Untreated, such
infections can cause serious dermatological problems, and in advanced
cases may lead to blindness. In certain areas of tropical Africa the
blindness caused by onchocerciasis is called <er>river
blindness</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onchorynchus</ent>⟦br⟧
